      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Distinct weak layers exist in the bottom section of the snowpack on west, north and east facing slopes, in particular above approximately 2000 m. <br/> <br/> Towards its surface, the snowpack consists of faceted crystals, especially on shady slopes at elevated altitudes. <br/> <br/> Outgoing longwave radiation during the night will be severely restricted. As a consequence of high relative humidity the snowpack can not consolidate, especially below approximately 2200 m. <br/> <br/> In steep terrain there is a danger of falling on the hard snow surface. This applies at high altitude."
      },
      "source": {
        "provider": {
          "name": "LWD K\u00e4rnten",
          "website": "https://lawinenwarndienst.ktn.gv.at/?lang=en"
        }
      },
